Going for the 2nd option, i did the following, using custom series with dummy data to do coord conversion and move my graphic:

```
{
    type: 'custom',
    coordinateSystem: 'geo',
    data: [[0, 0]],
    renderItem: function (params, api) {
        var lt = api.coord([-180, 90]), rb = api.coord([180, -90]);
        return {type:'image', style: {image: 'url...', x:lt[0], y:lt[1], width:rb[0]-lt[0], height:rb[1]-lt[1]}}
    }
}
```

The movement is smooth and it works as intended if only lags due to image size.
Probably if i return nothing and alter transforms on an underlying picture instead, there will be no lag (as panzoom.js has none).
It would still be tricky to get picture-to-geojson alignment and scaleLimit right, though.

I think i'll explore other options for production, but it was still great to be able to preview the desired result.

